==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic, from Indo-European.  Cognate with Old High German ''gor'', Middle (and modern) Dutch [[goor]], Old Norse ''gor'', and outside the Germanic languages with Welsh [[gôr]] ‘pus’.

===Pronunciation===
